Rating: 4
Made this for dinner for 8 people. Those reviewers who are getting a thick fudge-like result are using a chocolate with too high % of cocoa. I used 60% cocoa chips and it turned out great. The cream should be hot enough to be able to stick a finger in and not burn yourself but not want to keep your finger there either. Too hot and it will cook the yolks and make a mess. I never strain the custard, just keep as much white out of the yolks as possible and whip constantly while cooking (and do NOT heat to 160...150 is enough). I agree with several other reviewers; don't bother to melt the chocolate - just toss the chips into the hot custard and stir with a whisk (off the heat) and they melt right in. I also whipped all 4 egg whites and whisked them into the final product a little at a time until I got the right fluffy consistency and taste for me - turned out to be probably 2 of the whites. Got great reviews. Addition of some Baileys/Chambord/etc would be good.

