Rating: 4
WOW WOW WOW... this mousse is utterly fantastic! Every mouthful is heaven. Other than heating the custard only to 150 degrees (thank you everyone for recommending that), I followed the directions to a tee. It came out fluffy and chocolatey, a perfect mousse. For an added touch, spoon it into edible white chocolate cups. Melt 1 cup chips to 1 tbs shortening for 1 minute in the microwave on 70% power, then add'l 10-15 seconds bursts if not melted. Then paint with a pastry brush onto foil muffin cups. It will take about three batches of the melted white chocolate to make ~20 cups and use all the mousse (don't do it all at once because it hardens). Let set and then chill in the fridge. It was a bit harder to eat it this way, but mini foil (not paper) candy cups would work well. I also topped it with Kahlua whipped cream (whip 1/2 cup cream, 1/2 tbs. butter and 1/2 tbs Kahlua). I served these at a girls' night gathering and saved some for my hubby and kids, and everyone LOVED it. I will make this again and again. Perfect!!!!

