I was very pleased with this recipe. It was my first time making chocolate mousse and it turned out great. I even had a five year old eat it because he thought it tasted like chocolate ice cream. I would say that the most important part of this recipe to follow is the heating up of the custard to the temperature they suggest in the recipe. Heat it over LOW heat and keep a close eye on it. It only takes a minute or two to reach the temperature, then get it the heck off the heat and pour it into another bowl to cool. If you let it get any hotter, it was turn into scrambled eggs. My custard turned out good, but I could see how it wanted to start turning into eggs. I saved it just in time.

